      "translations": {
        "en.sayed-athar-husain-rizvi-&-sayed-maqsood-athar": {
          "segments": [
            "From my father (ra) through Saʿd ibn ʿAbdullāh, from Muʿāwiyah ibn Ḥukaim, from Muʿammar ibn Khallād, from Abū al-Ḥasan al-Riḍā (AS), from his father, who said that Abū ʿAbdullāh (AS) stated: \"The salvation of a believer lies in safeguarding his tongue.\" And Amīr al-Muʾminīn (AS) said: \"Whoever safeguards his tongue, Allah will conceal his faults.\""
          ],
